<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-38-0820 </DOCNO><TEXT>Material for cytological investigation was obtained from 115 patientswith pulmonary spheroidal formations with the help of fine (0.7-1.2 mmdiameter) and superfine (0.4-0.6 mm diameter) needles. Positive and cytologicalresults in malignant tumors were obtained in 87.6 % of the patients,in benign tumors - in 70 %. There were no serious complications. Themain advantage of puncture with fine and superfine needles is its safetyduring puncture of all zones including that at the radix pulmonis richin blood vessels.</TEXT></DOC>